# Production / native-app build configuration.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.production` and fill in the value, then rebuild.
# (`.env.production` is git-ignored; this `.example` is committed as documentation.)
#
# VITE_API_BASE is the absolute origin where the AI parsing endpoint lives —
# i.e. the URL of your deployed Cloudflare Pages site that serves
# functions/api/complete.js.
#
# - WEB build (the site itself): leave this EMPTY. The site calls /api/complete
#   on its own origin, so a relative path already works.
# - NATIVE app build (Capacitor Android/iOS): you MUST set this. The app's
#   webview runs at https://localhost, so a relative /api/complete goes nowhere
#   and AI parsing silently falls back to the offline parser.
#
# Example (replace with your real deployed domain):
# VITE_API_BASE=https://eat-sleep-train-repeat.pages.dev
VITE_API_BASE=
